The chairman of the Independent Petroleum Marketers Association of Nigeria (IPMAN), Benin Depot, Edo State, Baba Abdul-hamid Saliu, has been abducted, his driver shot dead. Saliu, elected depot chairman on Thursday, was abducted on Monday evening from his Jattu residence in Etsako West by about six gunmen who came in two unmarked vehicles, it was said.   Soldier shot, many injured in Gombe clash     OAU student: Police withdraw murder charge against Adedoyin     11 to die by hanging in Niger   The kidnappers overpowered and injured Saliu’s security personnel. Police spokesman Bello Kontongs confirmed the attack.